<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,258,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,219,259,283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Male.</emphasis>
Body stout. Head short, frontis verticis slightly oblique backwards. Fastigium verticis conical, apex obtusely rounded, furrowed in midline. Eyes subglobular, projecting forwards. Apical segment of maxillary palpus slightly longer than subapical one, apex slightly enlarged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,258,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[330,410,366,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,938,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[264,1323,938,1903]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis angustisulcus sp. nov., male holotype: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. pronotum in lateral view; C. tenth abdominal tergite in dorsal view; D. apex of abdomen in lateral view; E. cercus in lateral view; F. s ubgenital plate in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212798/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Figs. 
<number box="[399,410,366,390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B) projecting, anterior margin slightly straight, anterior and middle sulci indistinct, posterior transverse sulcus comparatively distinct, metazona conspicuously raised and enlarged, posterior margin obtusely rounded; posterior area of paranota broadened, without humeral sinus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,258,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Procoxa with a spine, all femora without spines on ventral margins, protibiae with 
<number box="[1131,1145,474,498]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="4.0">4</number>
spines on inner and outer margins of ventral surface separately; apex with a pair of ventral spurs; tibial tympana open on both sides, elongate. Mesotibiae with 
<number box="[338,352,546,570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="2.0">2</number>
spines on inner side and 
<number box="[631,645,546,570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="5.0">5</number>
spines on outer side of ventral margin, and with a pair of ventral apical spurs. Posttibia with a pair of dorsal apical spurs, and 
<number box="[756,770,582,606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of ventral apical spurs, right post leg damaged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,258,894]" box="[199,1239,618,642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">Tegmina brachypterous, completely hidden under metazona of pronotum; hind wings absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,258,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Tenth abdominal tergite (
<figureCitation box="[481,555,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,938,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[264,1323,938,1903]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis angustisulcus sp. nov., male holotype: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. pronotum in lateral view; C. tenth abdominal tergite in dorsal view; D. apex of abdomen in lateral view; E. cercus in lateral view; F. s ubgenital plate in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212798/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Figs. 
<number box="[544,555,654,678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D) projecting, comparatively long, basal half broad, the middle constricted, apical half slightly enlarged laterally; apices of the lateral lobes obtusely rounded, the notch on posterior margin narrower and longer, length more than 
<number box="[596,610,726,750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="2.0">2</number>
times of its width. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1096,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,938,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[264,1323,938,1903]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis angustisulcus sp. nov., male holotype: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. pronotum in lateral view; C. tenth abdominal tergite in dorsal view; D. apex of abdomen in lateral view; E. cercus in lateral view; F. s ubgenital plate in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212798/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Fig. 
<number box="[1086,1096,726,750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F) elongate, basal area broad, posterior margin triangularly concave. Styli shorter on apices of lateral margins of subgenital plate. Genitalia sclerotized, longer than tenth abdominal tergite, apex slightly enlarged, quadratus, the centre of dorsal margin with a deep notch. Cercus (
<figureCitation box="[402,477,834,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,938,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[264,1323,938,1903]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis angustisulcus sp. nov., male holotype: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. pronotum in lateral view; C. tenth abdominal tergite in dorsal view; D. apex of abdomen in lateral view; E. cercus in lateral view; F. s ubgenital plate in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212798/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Figs. 
<number box="[466,477,834,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, E) mostly exposed, but not concealed by tenth abdominal tergite, short, basal area stouter, apex obtusely rounded; subapical area with a blunt hook (
<figureCitation box="[887,950,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[264,1322,938,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[264,1323,938,1903]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sinocyrtaspis angustisulcus sp. nov., male holotype: A. pronotum in dorsal view; B. pronotum in lateral view; C. tenth abdominal tergite in dorsal view; D. apex of abdomen in lateral view; E. cercus in lateral view; F. s ubgenital plate in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212798/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="84">
Fig. 
<number box="[939,950,870,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="84" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
