<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,592]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,429,454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species is allied to 
<taxonomicName box="[655,963,429,453]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Sinocyrtaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycercus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[655,963,429,453]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">Sinocyrtaspis brachycercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[970,1060,429,453]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[970,1060,429,453]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs in the following: disc of pronotum with a pair of longitudinal brown stripes; posterior margin of male tenth abdominal tergite with a narrow and long notch (length more than two times of it’s width); male cercus almost exposed, of unique shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1436,533,557]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,592]" box="[199,1436,533,557]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,533,557]" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is derived from male cercus morphology, Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1210,1286,534,557]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">angus’</emphasis>
and ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1349,1419,533,557]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="85">sulcus</emphasis>
’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
